< Review>
I purchased (2) Zodiac Flea and Collars for small dogs on July24th, 2018.  When I opened both boxes the collar were dry and colors of white and hard.  I figured maybe they might still work.  I gave my dogs a bath with the Flea shampoo and put the collars on both dogs.  After a few days the dogs still itched and the shampoo and the collars did not work.  It was a waist of money and time to buy the Advantage treatment shampoo for dogs and puppies and the Zodiac Flea and Tick Collars.  I threw away my receipts thinking it was a waist of time to go back and complain.  I will never return to this store again.</Review>

< Text>
Great vision care! We have been coming here for a several years and the vision care has always been excellent. The optometrist explains everything in simple terms and provides all the necessary information to make decisions regarding your eye care (i.e. Lasik procedures, contacts, type of frames, etc.).  If needed they follow-up with the primary health insurance for ophthalmologist referrals. The staff has extensive knowledge and thoroughly explains your options based on your prescription for lenses, add-ons, etc. They have a wide variety of frames available.  Overall this place is great!<//Text>

<Rate>1<//Rate>< review>
My husband was desperate to get this new glasses within a reasonable time. We had called around and most places told us 8 days to get new glasses. This was not acceptable since he cannot see without them. We called Vision Express and they said it would be no more than 48 hrs. We where excited, 48 hrs was ok with us! Better than 8 days!

So we rushed down there! They had a good selection and reasonable prices. We made sure they where open on Saturday and they said they would call us when the glasses came in. We asked more than once to make sure we where not hearing things! My husband has been suffering from a severe headache because his other glasses where ruined.Whew we couldnt wait!

Saturday rolled around and NO CALL! We called them but they closed early. They were no open Sunday or Monday for Holiday. So finally its Tuesday and we want an explanation. They said "sorry we got too busy and forgot to call you". My husband told them that wasnt good enough we had asked them more than once when we came in there, they said "we know you couldnt see and werent feeling good but we got too busy".

Not a good enough answer for me folks! I am a business owner and when I say I am going to do something by a certain date I do it! No excuses! I will not be going here again!</review>

Rosie works tomorrow from 9:30-6:30 and you can make an appointment if you would like as well.\n\nThank you for your service.  We are a family (military as well) owned business.  The quality of our barbers is superior and we feel our prices are more than fair.  Once you try the others I think you may be back.  Best of luck to you in the meantime.'}</response><Rate>3</Rate><text>Just got my haircut at Crown about an hour ago.  Great atmosphere.  My barber [Rose?] was great, very kind and definitely listened to me.  So if I hadn't come home to the screwed up mustache, as seen in the picture, the rating would definitely have a 4---strictly due to the price.  I blame it on myself for not noticing at the barber shop when she handed me the mirror but I was looking more at the haircut itself.

I chose the barbershop because they had better ratings and the other reviews said they did a military discount---what I didn't realize is the discount is for active duty only.

I am a retired Marine mostly living as a nomad and spent the last 9 months in my RV all over the US.  Admittedly not ever in a big city where prices are no doubt much more expensive.  I get my haircut every 2-3 weeks and always look for a local barbershop with good ratings.  I always get both the hair and beard cut/trimmed.

The most expensive cut I had was in Memphis and Vermont for $18.  Most of the east coast all the way up to Maine was $15 for both hair and beard.

I spent three months in South Padre Island TX which, like Coronado, is also a beach and tourist town---I was always charged $12 and gave a $20 to include the tip.  I just left Eloy AZ after a month there, it's just north of Tucson---same cost, $12, $20 with tip.

I spent $40 today and that's the reason for the intended 4 rating.  I have absolutely no doubt the bad moustache trim is an aberration and would try again if not for the price.  $25 for the haircut and $8 for the beard trim in my mind is too much.  [I always give a good tip and always will as I recognize how blessed I am to have a cost of living adjusted retirement.]

Bottomline is I'm going to spend a lot of time here in Coronado as that is where the girlfriend is.  While I love that Crown is within walking distance there is no way I'm spending $40 every two-three weeks---guess I'll be driving to a nearby base.<//text>< user>

I am not from around Humbolt, however when I was visiting a friend at CSUH my car broke down.I was freaking out because I needed to drive home to Sacramento. I called Pro Pacific and I spoke with Ford, he was so nice and he offered to have me come in and see what they could do even though they were fully booked for the day. Travelling down from Vancouver Island on Hwy 101, vacation road trip, when my exhaust pipe failed. The only place open on Saturday I could find was Pro Pacific Auto. I stopped by in the morning and they were very busy and I could see a line up of vehicles and customers there. I was stationed at the Marine Corps Base for the last 2.5 yrs.  I live in San Diego, and I elected to buy a used RV and live on the Base RV Park vs. get an apartment.   I have never owned an RV in my life.  I bought a used 07 Class A Fleetwood.  Over the course of the 2.5 yrs I lived there, RV Depot saved me time and time again.  Over the course of my time there I had an AC go out the first summer, then the other go out the second summer,  my public power source caught on fire, my power inlet on the coach shorted out, eventually my levelers gave out and I broke the shower handle. I'm now retired and back in San Diego.   Thank you, Vince and RV Depot!!   Sincerely Frank Percy, LCDR, (RET)</Review>

I recently purchased my 2013 Outback from a major RV dealer in Orange County.  That major dealer serviced it for me earlier this year.  I needed some other maintenance work done on my coach and Vince noticed the O.C. dealer never packed the wheel bearings I was charged $500.00 for.  I was able to get a refund from the major dealer but best of all my wheels didn't fall off on our following vacations.  We were safe thanks to RV Depot!

I will never go back to the dealer again.  Vince is super knowledgeable about RV's and is always eager to please.  Pricing is very reasonable and more than fair.  He just sold me and put 4 new high quality tires on. I was expecting to pay much more and was so surprised at the low price I told him to add on another  $100.00.  He smiled and respectfully turned down my offer.  As a business owner myself, Vince displays the same honesty and integrity I portray in my business.  I consider him a close Friend now and find having work done on my trailer a very pleasurable experience.

Thank you Vince, Kim and the rest of the team.  See you on next visit!<//Text>

< review>
My husband and I had just moved back to 29 on a Saturday and our ac went out on us, just completely died. I was trying to go through another business but they were not on top of it. By the time Tuesday afternoon had rolled around it still hadn't gotten fixed. I finally saw one of rv depots vans so I decided to give them a call to see when they could do it. I wish that I had dealt with them from the beginning. Kim was so helpful and friendly, she called Vince and told him what was going on while was on the phone with her and she said he would give me a call back to give me better in-site to what they could do. He called me back within a half hour! I was so impressed because the other place I had to call 5 times on Tuesday with no one getting back to me. When he has explaining to me what he thought it was, he said he would call around to find a unit for us. Again he called me back within the hour and said he had found one but wanted to make sure I wanted it to be replaced because the drive was 2 and half hours round trip. This was at 4 in the afternoon and he didn't care that it would have him working late, as long as we could have our air fixed. Vince and Austin came out the NEXT DAY and had it completely replaced. Then we had a breaker/converter problem going on and he came back to check it out. Once we thought we had it figured out, he still proceeded to call me to check up on us and the air. The way that Vince and Kim handled their business is hands down one of the best places I have ever dealt with. I HIGHLY recommend to have your work done through rv depot. You can always expect honesty, integrity, efficiency, and a friendly environment. The way they helped us made it feel like I was family they were helping. Thank you so much for all that you did for me and my family Vince!<//review>

<UserId.>102166419214716789603</UserId.><Date>1577770769250</Date><pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMpo1VsNwbfR04nMpwGjXi4zjesPP81Dg-4OD6E=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//pics>< review>
Let me preface this with I am Chinese, travelled to 39 countries and have eaten Chinese food in many, many places. I saw the reviews on this site and let go of expectations for dinner. The "family style ma po tofu  with veggies" was rather flavorless with the frozen trio (corn, peas, carrots); we looked for chili pepper sauce. The Szechuan eggplant was rather tasty minus any semblance to Szechuan flavors. With added chili sauce, black pepper and salt, these two hot, gooey dishes warmed and satiated us on a cold night. Plenty of left over, too.
The server reminded me of my grumpy teens; it was sort of comical. She was attending to both the restaurant AND bar; that's a lot on a little lady with 4-5 tables to serve, concurrently. Kudos to her. One thumbs up for the experience.
Took left overs back to the inn and my teens wouldn't eat more than a bite. They rather microwaved their instant noodle bowls instead. Hehe. Thumbs down from them for all 3 items, even the rice.

The pu'er (?) tea was drinkable but truly poor quality. Serving plates, a mish mash of styles, need work. Poor presentation.
Definitely not a place for discriminating taste. Hope this helps.< /review>

My review is based on the customer service manager Maria.
